    "created_at": "2018-04-03T11:44:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-04-03T11:44:05Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A more appropriate change would be to add a `DestructibleCrowdsale` that, perhaps, inherits from `FinalizableCrowdsale` in order to destroy itself after it's been completed.\r\n\r\nMaking a crowdsale destructible by default isn't a reasonable decision, but I've created a separate issue to track the `DestructibleCrowdsale` addition: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/issues/862\r\n\r\n@jacktang  In general, all constructors are `public payable` to allow someone to send ether to the contract (and anything that inherits it) at deploy-time. Probably a combination of convention and simplicity, but I'd be interested in knowing for sure.",
